1601956800.title: Bargain Hunt
1601956800.descr: Two teams of amateur antique collectors meet at an antiques fair to compete to make the largest profit from a three hundred pound budget. Once the contestants have done the shopping for their own items, the experts then take any leftover money and go shopping for more antiques which is 'bonus buys'. The teams then have to decide whether or not to take these items to auction.

1601959500.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1601959500.descr: Classic British sitcom following the misadventures of a trio of elderly men from a Yorkshire village who never tire of playing tricks on their fellow townspeople. The series is Britain's longest-running comedy programme and has received many praises for its family-friendly humour and portrayal of older people.

1601961300.title: Call the Midwife
1601961300.descr: Period drama series set in East London in the 1950s, following the life and work of a young midwife Jenny Lee and her colleagues at the Nonnatus House nursing convent. They serve the poor society of Poplar, London. Their main duty is to help bring safe birth to women and help them look after their newborns.

1601964600.title: DIY SOS: The Big Build
1601964600.descr: Take a family in desperate need of help in their home. Add some local tradesmen, lot's of generosity and a bucket load of community spirit. You've got yourself the recipe for DIY SOS. Nick Knowles, along with him team of home improvement experts, and lot's of happy volunteers from the communities of Britain pitch in to make life changing modifications to the homes of families who need them most.

Inspector Mallory arrests Mrs Fitzgerald for murdering her own father.

1602007200.title: Last of the Summer Wine
1602007200.descr: Clegg is writing his memoirs, but is having trouble remembering people's names; Clegg, Truly and Billy meet a man who wants to sail to Ilkley in an inflatable swan, unfortunately it has developed a puncture which Entwistle repairs; Clegg climbs a tree so he can see the church clock, unfortunately he gets stuck; Tom and Entwistle try to cheer Smiler up after he has been dumped by Hermione.

1602010800.title: Unforgotten
1602010800.descr: A cop show which gets a lot of things right. The leads are convincing and realistic, the plots are complex but not too complicated, the procedural elements are spot on and the basic humanity of the victims, their families and the other characters is compelling. Nicola Walker plays DCI Cassie Stuart and she is partnered with DS Sunil "Sunny" Khan (Sanjeev Bhaskar) as they are tasked with investigating crimes from the past.

1602013500.title: Happy Valley
1602013500.descr: A therapist tries to get to the bottom of why Catherine felt the need to attend Tommy Lee Royce's mother's funeral, while the discovery of a new body makes John nervous. Elsewhere, Tommy urges Frances to use any means necessary to make Catherine's life a misery.

1602016500.title: W1A
1602016500.descr: Following on from the BAFTA award-winning Twenty Twelve: the BBC has a new Head of Values, Ian Fletcher and he's been given the huge task of sorting the corporation out, he has to "restructure" it. The BBC is becoming under a huge load of pressure with the content that they produce. This British comedy is the BBC realising where it goes wrong and is essentially criticising itself.

1602018600.title: Our Girl
1602018600.descr: Set in the time of Britain's withdrawal from Afghanistan, Our Girl follows the journeys of female medics. It all began when teenage girl Molly found herself in the army's recruitment office, after being sick in the doorway having celebrated her eighteenth birthday. Since then, there has been incredible displays of love, laughs, and loss.
